 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: BAO-2: Remove legacy footer injection for ACP-enabled commands — single projection algebra (INV-BUDGET-009, INV-GUIDANCE-001). BACKGROUND: Currently ACP commands produce action-first output AND get a legacy M(t) footer appended, resulting in redundant representation. The agent sees the next action twice: once in the ACP body (structurally first) and once in the footer (appended). This wastes ~100 tokens of context. The ACP methodology context blocks (from ACP-9) already include M(t) data. The footer adds no new information. APPROACH: In maybe_inject_footer() (commands/mod.rs), check if the command produced ACP output (the _acp JSON field). If so, skip footer injection entirely. The ACP output already contains the action (from compute_action_from_store) and methodology context (from methodology_context_blocks). The legacy footer remains for non-ACP commands during the migration period. Tests: (A) ACP status output has NO footer appended (no M(t) line after the evidence pointer). (B) Non-ACP commands (observe, harvest) still get the footer. (C) -q flag still works (suppresses methodology context). (D) No information loss: every datum in the legacy footer is available in the ACP context blocks. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs (maybe_inject_footer)"
